<p local-id=3D"6e8686b50bc3"><strong>Widget 6 =E2=80=94 Latency Monitoring<=
/strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"48f919b519c9">Displays average API response time over time. =
Identifies endpoints or time periods where the API is responding slowly.</p=
>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"69f085b9d093">Visualization: Line chart</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"05076036669c">NRQL Query:</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5db157b2280d">sql</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">SELECT =
average(duration) FROM Transaction TIMESERIES</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"58e90417a60a" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-5.ErrorRateMon=
itoring">5. Error Rate Monitoring</h2>
<p local-id=3D"b58f1dcb6cbc">Error rate represents the percentage of failed=
 requests (4xx and 5xx responses) relative to total API requests. It is one=
 of the most important indicators of API reliability and is the primary sig=
nal used to trigger alerts and initiate incident response.</p>
<p local-id=3D"dbc0372019df">A rising error rate may indicate:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"15516dfe30be">Backend application failures or unhandled exce=
ptions (5xx)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b78225a43025">Incorrect client usage, invalid parameters, or=
 authentication failures (4xx)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d662c6b43079">Infrastructure issues such as EC2 instance fai=
lure or ALB misconfiguration</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"23f2130b3fd3">Sudden traffic spikes overwhelming the applica=
tion</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"33bccaeb3432"><strong>Monitored Conditions:</strong></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"8=
b6ce5c5-14e1-4bf7-ab03-47e04112f277" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"5cec0a9a081d">Condition</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"74986ab125cf">Signal</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a0e86d169c3c">Action</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1aa8ac61a366">Rising server errors (5xx)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"37176011aece">Backend application failures</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"02e2d744ecba">Immediate investigation =E2=80=94 check applic=
ation logs and EC2 health</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4c5713b5c37e">Increased client errors (4xx)</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e370d354e8eb">Invalid requests or auth failures</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e79b5eeb7d96">Review client request patterns; check API inpu=
t validation</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ec6483c0795f">Sudden drop in successful responses (2xx)</p><=
/td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5ab9a505dcfe">Possible API or infrastructure outage</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"268e14ba19d0">Check ALB health checks and EC2 instance statu=
s</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f435b63aa455">Abnormal request spikes</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"584acedd84bb">Unexpected traffic surge</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2b71b469d036">Review ALB access logs; assess whether auto-sc=
aling is needed</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
