<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"d3df057dd6ae" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-7.IncidentMana=
gement">7. Incident Management</h2>
<p local-id=3D"ca15d9a0a131">When an alert is triggered, the following inci=
dent workflow is followed:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0a45c5ba133b"><strong>Detection</strong> =E2=80=94 New Relic=
 monitoring detects an anomaly and triggers the configured alert condition<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"214ce87af4b1"><strong>Notification</strong> =E2=80=94 Alert =
notification is sent to the on-call DevOps engineer via the configured noti=
fication channel (email, Slack, PagerDuty)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1aace473b289"><strong>Investigation</strong> =E2=80=94 Engin=
eer reviews the New Relic dashboard to identify the affected metric, time o=
f onset, and impacted endpoints</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d80e033e74ea"><strong>Root Cause Identification</strong> =E2=
=80=94 Application logs, ALB health check status, and EC2 instance metrics =
are reviewed to identify the underlying cause</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5f387066d5fa"><strong>Service Restoration</strong> =E2=80=94=
 Fix is applied (restart service, fix configuration, scale resources) and r=
esolution is confirmed via the dashboard</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"26ec6b5fe74d"><strong>Post-Incident Review</strong> =E2=80=
=94 Root cause, timeline, and preventive actions are documented; alert thre=
sholds are tuned if needed</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 local-id=3D"82bb4a963240" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-8.Dashboard"><=
strong>8. Dashboard</strong></h2><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wr=
apper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"c=
onfluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"image-20260321-145846.png" wi=
dth=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"9dbadfbba3441e738a55dbcc9c6148b62455c64=
a692b9b52d3e32657fab8b3db" data-image-src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/w=
iki/download/attachments/1886978051/image-20260321-145846.png?version=3D1&a=
mp;modificationDate=3D1774181000279&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data=
-height=3D"438" data-width=3D"1024" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" dat=
a-linked-resource-id=3D"1886978061" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data=
-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"=
image-20260321-145846.png" data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wi=
ki" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-co=
ntainer-id=3D"1886978051" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" data=
-media-id=3D"f9d3a15a-8240-4f7d-9da5-d0f9042684ce" data-media-type=3D"file"=
 height=3D"200"></span>
<p local-id=3D"64d62795a29e"><em>Key observations visible in the dashboard:=
</em></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3f05be5c95a9"><strong>HTTP Request Errors:</strong> 6 backen=
d (500) errors and 5 frontend (400) errors recorded since 1 hour ago =E2=80=
=94 confirming both server-side and client-side error tracking is active</p=
></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"335e884815ed"><strong>2xx Successful Responses:</strong> Tim=
e-series area chart showing successful response trends over the past hour w=
ith consistent traffic patterns</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5bf2dc364a6e"><strong>Error Rate (Log Levels):</strong> Thre=
e billboard widgets show 466 INFO logs, 442 DEBUG logs, and 8 ERROR logs =
=E2=80=94 providing log-level breakdown alongside request metrics</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8cdb1e3e42a5"><strong>Response Handover Time:</strong> Line =
chart displaying API response latency trends over time =E2=80=94 useful for=
 identifying latency spikes and performance degradation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"06e55736629a"><strong>Succeeded vs Failed Requests:</strong>=
 Donut chart showing the distribution of successful vs failed requests; the=
 breakdown by instance IP confirms traffic is being distributed across mult=
iple targets (ip-172-31-66-88 at 45.69%, ip-172-31-18-116 at 26.4%, and zar=
gordessel-curat at 5.67%)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"040e4bf86ee4"><strong>Total Request Count:</strong> Billboar=
d widget showing 456 Transactions processed in the past hour =E2=80=94 the =
primary volume metric</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a878d5e730a7"><strong>HTTP State Count:</strong> Horizontal =
bar chart listing specific HTTP events including Server heartbeat succeeded=
 (811), Server heartbeat started (811), account login events (280), and a 4=
04 error entry =E2=80=94 providing granular per-event visibility</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1806af778350"><strong>HTTP Requests Per Second by Region:</s=
trong> Time-series chart showing request rate distribution across regions o=
ver time</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"96acdb65702e"><strong>Connection Count:</strong> Time-series=
 chart showing active, injected, and right connection counts =E2=80=94 usef=
ul for monitoring concurrent connection patterns and detecting connection s=
pikes</p></li>
</ul>
