<h2 local-id=3D"b47d63300714" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-9.Implementati=
onTimeline"><strong>9. Implementation Timeline</strong></h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"9=
8ee7af3-1545-4d86-8d10-3db690dbed4a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"e9cd915fcbbe">Phase</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"c06eefc3882a">Task</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"897a133dc8dc">Duration</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a96d76b11bbc">Phase 1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"00214d20efef">New Relic agent installation and configuration=
 on EC2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c8befa8110d8">30 minutes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8a2759929c37">Phase 2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ea6e759caba6">Dashboard creation =E2=80=94 all 6 widgets con=
figured with NRQL queries</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"85751545978b">45 minutes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2c58ae811069">Phase 3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ec4ff5987807">Alert policy configuration =E2=80=94 4xx, 5xx,=
 availability, and drop alerts</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cc456938ae4b">30 minutes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"72731471f990">Phase 4</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"6e52032fe14e">Testing and validation =E2=80=94 traffic gener=
ation, alert trigger verification</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c3b564aa3621">30 minutes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8661fec3da55"><strong>Total</strong></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"668179d08376"></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0707d34c4199"><strong>~2 hours 15 minutes</strong></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"06963fa8d28c" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-10.ContinuousI=
mprovement"><strong>10. Continuous Improvement</strong></h2>
<p local-id=3D"6d3e29792e56">The following enhancements are planned for sub=
sequent iterations of the monitoring implementation:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1dfd9353d9e8"><strong>Distributed Tracing:</strong> Implemen=
t New Relic distributed tracing to track individual requests across all ser=
vices =E2=80=94 enabling per-request root cause analysis</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"aab60ad38056"><strong>Centralised Logging:</strong> Integrat=
e application logs with New Relic Logs or AWS CloudWatch Logs for searchabl=
e, correlated log analysis alongside metrics</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"28e895f89aa0"><strong>Prometheus + Grafana Integration:</str=
ong> Add Prometheus metrics endpoint to the FastAPI application and visuali=
ze in Grafana as an open-source monitoring alternative</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d8b04cb52098"><strong>Auto-Scaling Alerts:</strong> Configur=
e CloudWatch alarms linked to ALB request metrics to trigger EC2 Auto Scali=
ng =E2=80=94 ensuring capacity responds to real demand</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5146cde8ef14"><strong>SLA / SLO Monitoring:</strong> Define =
Service Level Objectives (e.g., 99.9% availability, P95 latency &lt; 200ms)=
 and add New Relic SLO widgets to the dashboard</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"68543dbac379"><strong>Alert Tuning:</strong> Refine alert th=
resholds based on observed baseline traffic patterns after 2=E2=80=934 week=
s of production data</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3672e1efcf64"><strong>Automated Remediation:</strong> Config=
ure New Relic webhooks to trigger AWS Lambda functions for automatic remedi=
ation actions =E2=80=94 such as restarting a failed EC2 service on 5xx aler=
t</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"ae46418875dc" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-11.ExpectedDel=
iverables"><strong>11. Expected Deliverables</strong></h2>
<p local-id=3D"aa8965b468d6"><strong>Dashboard Screenshots:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e335b6322619">API request trends (time-series area chart)</p=
></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3be908bfe903">HTTP status code distribution (bar chart)</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"aff3f931f026">Error rate over time (billboard + time-series)=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"a42b48174f62"><strong>Alert Configuration Screenshots:</stro=
ng></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"258e0640c611">5xx error rate alert policy</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5ccfac10927b">4xx error rate alert policy</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3989a60ece49">API availability alert policy</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"67467179841d"><strong>Confluence Documentation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"917cdfdc2b62">Requirement analysis page</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c33e0e6e724a">Technical documentation page</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"adbce879df0a">Error rate vs status code explanation</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"1bbc56cfceaf"><strong>Demo Video (2=E2=80=933 minutes):</str=
ong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"46030afae9f6">Dashboard overview walkthrough</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"53bb13b6d163">Error monitoring demonstration</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"970726d4598d">Alert configuration explanation</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"bd284e86b21f" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-12.Conclusion"=
><strong>12. Conclusion</strong></h2>
<h2 local-id=3D"1052dcadea79" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-12.1Summary">1=
2.1 Summary</h2>
<p local-id=3D"54bcbd7c43a5">The Bookstore API monitoring dashboard was suc=
cessfully implemented using New Relic APM, providing comprehensive operatio=
nal visibility into API health, performance, and error behavior. The implem=
entation achieves all defined objectives within the 3-hour time constraint.=
</p>
<p local-id=3D"9ffd4314019d"><strong>Key achievements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"513952864ee9">Real-time API request volume monitoring and tr=
end visualization</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dd0acebbb355">HTTP status code distribution tracking (2xx, 4=
xx, 5xx)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"683f8ddf572f">Error rate monitoring with time-series visuali=
zation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b11563f83ff5">Four alert policies configured for proactive i=
ncident detection</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"92d98827a5c7">End-to-end observability from ALB request inge=
stion to New Relic dashboard</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"0c7c63a5a9f8">The monitoring setup gives the operations team=
 the tools to detect, investigate, and resolve API issues faster =E2=80=94 =
directly improving MTTD and MTTR and aligning with AWS Well-Architected pri=
nciples for operational excellence and reliability.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"b3263ba43376" id=3D"Task12-TechnicalDocument-12.2NextSteps"=
>12.2 Next Steps</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2a2ce3534ad2">Implement distributed tracing for per-request =
visibility across all API endpoints</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9ef13114bdb1">Define and monitor formal SLOs for API availab=
ility and response time</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"362e7aedbbdf">Integrate centralised log management with New =
Relic Logs or CloudWatch</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f58b2e6834c0">Automate alert-driven remediation using Lambda=
 functions triggered by New Relic webhooks</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
